<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-229-935  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 229 935.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Jan 2 1989 n398 p26(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Layers of connections will be sought in 1989. (network industryforecast)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Duffy, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The need to integrate LANs into enterprise-wide networks and toachieve interoperability among disparate LAN operating systemsdominate the networks market for 1989.andP;  The installed base of morethan 100,000 networks offers a beginning point.andP;  DEC, in 1989,will offer multivendor connectivity through its gateway products:DECnet SNA and VMS Ultrix.andP;  IBM's strategy appears to be to designthe corporate multivendor backbone network.andP;  IBM offers an OpenSystems Interconnect (OSI) product line, the 8232 LAN ChannelStation, which links IBM hosts to IBM and other vendors' LANs, andTCP-IP mainframe operating system protocol support.andP;  IBM'sToken-Ring LAN works as an open platform for third-partynetworking software and can link other networks into SNAenvironments.andP;  PC LAN market leader Novell Inc will expand its WANofferings.andP;  The Bridge Communications Div of 3Com offers variousconnectivity products.andP;  Banyan Systems Inc will release a tool kitof application programming interfaces.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (planning)International Business Machines Corp. (planning)Novell Inc. (planning)Bridge Communications Inc. (planning)Banyan Systems Inc. (planning).andO;Ticker:    IBM; DEC; NOVL; COMS.andO;Topic:     NetworksLocal Area NetworksForecastingPreview of Coming YearNew ProductProduct DevelopmentMarketConnectivity.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>